e a new project you can review that procedure from the <strong>Minibot <\/strong>tutorial <a href=\"\/creating-the-project\/\">here<\/a>.<\/p>\n\n\n\n<p>This new robot will require three subsystems:<\/p>\n\n\n\n<ol><li><strong><a href=\"\/drive-subsystem-3\/\">Drive Subsystem<\/a><\/strong><\/li><li><strong><a href=\"\/shooter-subsystem-2\/\" data-type=\"page\" data-id=\"2938\">Shooter Subsystem<\/a><\/strong><\/li><li><strong><a href=\"\/feeder-subsystem-2\/\">Feeder Subsystem<\/a><\/strong><\/li><\/ol>\n\n\n\n<p>You now have a decision to make. Creating the <strong>Drive Subsystem<\/strong> is a lot of work and, in reality, you probably won&#8217;t be needing to do this when working on the FRC robots. There is much to be learned by working on the <strong>Drive Subsystem<\/strong> and <strong>Arcade Drive<\/strong>, but if you would like to skip that part and get right to the meat of things, click <a href=\"\/starting-with-a-working-drive-subsyste\/\">here<\/a>.<\/p>\n\n\n\n<p>Otherwise, let&#8217;s dive in.<\/p>\n\n\n\n<p><a href=\"\/drive-subsystem-3\/\">Next: Drive Subsystem<\/a><\/p>\n","protected":false},"excerpt":{"rendered":"<p>In this tutorial you are going to learn to program the&nbsp;SwerveBot. This robot is significantly more sophisticated than the robot you programmed in the&nbsp;Minibot&nbsp;tutorial. This robot incorporates a swerve drive mechanism instead of the tank drive of the Minibot. The swerve drive consists of four independent wheels each of which can be rotated to any&hellip;&nbsp;<a href=\"http:\/\/gabybot.com\/swervebot\/\" class=\"\" rel=\"bookmark\">Read More &raquo;<span class=\"screen-reader-text\">SwerveBot<\/span><\/a><\/p>\n","protected":false},"author":2,"featured_media":0,"parent":0,"menu_order":0,"comment_status":"closed","ping_status":"closed","template":"","meta":{"neve_meta_sidebar":"","neve_meta_container":"","neve_meta_enable_content_width":"","neve_meta_content_width":0,"neve_meta_title_alignment":"","neve_meta_author_avatar